                            <comment id="16847924" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Fri, 24 May 2019 22:00:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is one of the hardest to test areas and since it often happens in less than ideal conditions it&apos;s also important to test reconnect under many different (possibly repeating) failure cases. This area is a bit of our soft under-shell, though developers have made many fixes and improvements over the years. This stuff works a lot more often than it used to in master.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have a few more of those fixes and improvements.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16849930" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Tue, 28 May 2019 17:00:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Pull request and patch for review:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/lucene-solr/pull/689&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/lucene-solr/pull/689&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/lucene-solr/pull/689&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://patch-diff.githubusercontent.com/raw/apache/lucene-solr/pull/689.patch&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16852049" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Thu, 30 May 2019 16:32:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t really have something I can commit, but I test this by forcing stop the world gc pauses, repeatedly with random time between, ensuring it tests real world gc pauses and tests them happening again during the reconnect phase.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s a bit of a hack to do this, how well it works depends on the garbage collector, it can take a very long time to run if you dont have great hardware, and so it&apos;s not really unit test material.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
